{
  "detail_href": "/docs/api/ops/diagonal/",
  "detail_json_href": "/api-data/ops/diagonal.json",
  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Return specified diagonals."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is 2-D, returns the diagonal of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " with the given offset,\ni.e., the collection of elements of the form "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a[i, i+offset]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".  If\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " has more than two dimensions, then the axes specified by "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nand "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " are used to determine the 2-D sub-array whose diagonal is\nreturned.  The shape of the resulting array can be determined by\nremoving "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and appending an index to the right equal\nto the size of the resulting diagonals."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In versions of NumPy prior to 1.7, this function always returned a new,\nindependent array containing a copy of the values in the diagonal."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In NumPy 1.7 and 1.8, it continues to return a copy of the diagonal,\nbut depending on this fact is deprecated. Writing to the resulting\narray continues to work as it used to, but a FutureWarning is issued."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Starting in NumPy 1.9 it returns a read-only view on the original array.\nAttempting to write to the resulting array will produce an error."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In some future release, it will return a read/write view and writing to\nthe returned array will alter your original array.  The returned array\nwill have the same type as the input array."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If you don't write to the array returned by this function, then you can\njust ignore all of the above."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If you depend on the current behavior, then we suggest copying the\nreturned array explicitly, i.e., use "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "we.diagonal(a).copy()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " instead\nof just "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.diagonal(a).html",
                "href": "",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "diagonal(a)",
                "text": "we.diagonal(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". This will work with both past and future\nversions of NumPy."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Array from which the diagonals are taken."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array_like",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Array from which the diagonals are taken."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "a",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Offset of the diagonal from the main diagonal.  Can be positive or\nnegative.  Defaults to main diagonal (0)."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Offset of the diagonal from the main diagonal.  Can be positive or\nnegative.  Defaults to main diagonal (0)."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "offset",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Axis to be used as the first axis of the 2-D sub-arrays from which\nthe diagonals should be taken.  Defaults to first axis (0)."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Axis to be used as the first axis of the 2-D sub-arrays from which\nthe diagonals should be taken.  Defaults to first axis (0)."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "axis1",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Axis to be used as the second axis of the 2-D sub-arrays from\nwhich the diagonals should be taken. Defaults to second axis (1)."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Axis to be used as the second axis of the 2-D sub-arrays from\nwhich the diagonals should be taken. Defaults to second axis (1)."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "axis2",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Parameters",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Parameters"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is 2-D, then a 1-D array containing the diagonal and of the\nsame type as "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is returned unless "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is a "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "matrix"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", in which case\na 1-D array rather than a (2-D) "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "matrix"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is returned in order to\nmaintain backward compatibility."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  },
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a.ndim > 2"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", then the dimensions specified by "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "axis1"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " and "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "axis2"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "\nare removed, and a new axis inserted at the end corresponding to the\ndiagonal."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "ndarray",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "If "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is 2-D, then a 1-D array containing the diagonal and of the\nsame type as "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is returned unless "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is a "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "matrix"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ", in which case\na 1-D array rather than a (2-D) "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "matrix"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is returned in order to\nmaintain backward compatibility."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "array_of_diagonals",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Returns",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
